        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:23PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 423 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 17 miles south of Spartanburg to 3 miles
northeast of Laurens to 13 miles northeast of Greenwood. Movement was
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Laurens, Clinton, Woodruff, Joanna, Buffalo, Waterloo, Rose Hill
State Park, Mountville, Kinards, and Enoree.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
